**Pitfall — import style**: Use `import type { ... }` not `import { ... }` since all imports from contracts are type-only in this module. This is both correct (no runtime Effect.js overhead) and consistent with how the shared package uses the contracts (it imports values in `model.ts` but those are actual runtime constants from `orchestration.ts`).

**Pitfall — `mutedForeground` approximations**: The CSS uses `color-mix()` with Tailwind color vars. The hex approximations `#696969` (light) and `#7d7d7d` (dark) are close but not exact. For the theme system this is acceptable — the JS override provides a close match, and these exact colors are only visible in the brief moment before JS loads (handled by the module-level `applyTheme()` call).

