**Pitfall — `@theme inline` tokens are Tailwind class utilities**: Adding `--color-sidebar` etc. to the `@theme inline` block makes `bg-sidebar`, `text-sidebar-foreground`, etc. available as Tailwind classes. This is optional but correct architecture — components can use these utility classes in future. Since `applyTheme()` sets `--sidebar` directly on `documentElement.style`, Tailwind's `bg-sidebar` (which reads `var(--sidebar)`) will automatically pick up the runtime value. No additional CSS work is needed.

**Pitfall — the `@theme inline` block does NOT control the fallback values**; the `:root` block does. The two insertions must both happen.

