# Plan: Custom Theme System for T3 Code Editor

## Context

T3 Code currently supports only a light/dark/system toggle — a CSS class on `<html>` combined with static CSS variables in `index.css`. There are no named color palettes, no per-surface color customization, and no theme selector UI. This change adds a full palette-level theme system with three built-in themes, a React provider/hook that applies themes as CSS custom properties at runtime, and a settings UI with visual preview swatches.

The new "t3-dark" and "t3-light" themes closely match the current CSS defaults (ensuring a seamless migration), while "t3-midnight" introduces a distinctive deep navy/blue-tinted palette.

---

## Architecture

- **Types** → `packages/contracts/src/theme.ts` (schema-only package, plain TS interfaces, no Effect runtime)
- **Data + helpers** → `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` (new subpath export `@t3tools/shared/theme`)
- **Application logic** → `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` (rewrite; module-level `useSyncExternalStore` pattern preserved; `applyTheme` now sets all CSS custom properties as inline styles on `:root`)
- **UI** → `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` (new; swatches + radio card pattern matching existing settings page)
- **Settings integration** → `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` (replace the Appearance section)
- **CSS** → `apps/web/src/index.css` (add new surface variables + `@theme inline` tokens as fallbacks/Tailwind utilities)

CSS inline styles (`document.documentElement.style.setProperty(...)`) take precedence over stylesheet rules, so the JS theme override cleanly supersedes the static `@variant dark` block for palette values — while the `.dark` class toggle is preserved to keep Tailwind's `dark:` variants working.

